English:  Extinctbirds1907 P42, The giant moa (Dinornis novaezealandiae) is an extinct species of ratite birds belonging to the moa family. It was endemic to New Zealand. In Rothschild's book 'Extinct Birds' this moa referred to as Dinornis ingens.

One-Eleventh Natural Size—restoration from skeleton and feathers
